3914	/* Call() is the core of Redis execution of a command.
3915	 *
3916	 * The following flags can be passed:
3917	 * CMD_CALL_NONE        No flags.
3918	 * CMD_CALL_PROPAGATE_AOF   Append command to AOF if it modified the dataset
3919	 *                          or if the client flags are forcing propagation.
3920	 * CMD_CALL_PROPAGATE_REPL  Send command to slaves if it modified the dataset
3921	 *                          or if the client flags are forcing propagation.
3922	 * CMD_CALL_PROPAGATE   Alias for PROPAGATE_AOF|PROPAGATE_REPL.
3923	 * CMD_CALL_FULL        Alias for SLOWLOG|STATS|PROPAGATE.
3924	 *
3925	 * The exact propagation behavior depends on the client flags.
3926	 * Specifically:
3927	 *
3928	 * 1. If the client flags CLIENT_FORCE_AOF or CLIENT_FORCE_REPL are set
3929	 *    and assuming the corresponding CMD_CALL_PROPAGATE_AOF/REPL is set
3930	 *    in the call flags, then the command is propagated even if the
3931	 *    dataset was not affected by the command.
3932	 * 2. If the client flags CLIENT_PREVENT_REPL_PROP or CLIENT_PREVENT_AOF_PROP
3933	 *    are set, the propagation into AOF or to slaves is not performed even
3934	 *    if the command modified the dataset.
3935	 *
3936	 * Note that regardless of the client flags, if CMD_CALL_PROPAGATE_AOF
3937	 * or CMD_CALL_PROPAGATE_REPL are not set, then respectively AOF or
3938	 * slaves propagation will never occur.
3939	 *
3940	 * Client flags are modified by the implementation of a given command
3941	 * using the following API:
3942	 *
3943	 * forceCommandPropagation(client *c, int flags);
3944	 * preventCommandPropagation(client *c);
3945	 * preventCommandAOF(client *c);
3946	 * preventCommandReplication(client *c);
3947	 *
